{
  "timestamp": "2026-07-21T01:36:38Z",
  "title": "Message and question flows, and a card you choose yourself",
  "type": "feature",
  "userRequest": "bien, pero las flechas para ir d eun lado a otro de las cartas no funcionan",
  "description": "Built the web app's two remaining entry points as real flows: 'quiero recibir un mensaje' draws with nothing asked of it, and 'tengo una pregunta específica' takes the question first and keeps it on screen above the answer. Both end in a spread of 22 face-down cards you move through and pick from — the deck is shuffled each visit, so position says nothing about the arcana and the choice is a real blind draw. The revealed page was rebuilt to match the web: star-rule dividers, a sage italic quote and centred body, all on Josefin Sans (bundled, no new dependency), with the arcana/name line dropped since the artwork already carries it.\n\nThe spread's movement is animated deliberately, not decoratively: every card shows the same back, so changing the index alone repaints an identical frame and the arrows read as broken. A first attempt only slid the row, which made the arriving card reach the middle still tilted and dim before snapping upright; it is now a continuous carousel where each slot interpolates its tilt, drop and dimming from one driver, and lands in the exact centre pose. slotSamples covers that with a test asserting the arriving pose equals the resting centre pose.\n\nAll five pages were deconstructed to pure composition — zero raw JSX, 790 lines down to 341 — across 24 components with 52 scenarios, and the untested pre-existing logic (dailyCard's day-rollover rules, the bilingual deck, date formatting) picked up 69 tests total.\n\nTwo notes for whoever picks this up. First, the shipped v6 .codeyam/seed-adapter.ts emits {\"localStorage\": {...}} but the binary parses adapter stdout as a FLAT key→value map (parse_local_storage_from_stdout, crates/control-api/src/seed.rs), so every seeded key landed as one entry literally named \"localStorage\" and seeded scenarios silently captured their EMPTY state. The adapter is patched locally to emit the flat map; a `refresh-seed-adapter --force` would revert it. Second, animation transients are unverified by capture — the tooling settles the page before screenshotting, so the card flip and the spread's slide are confirmed by logic and endpoints only, never observed.",
